Package: DoseOptDesign
Title: Utility Score Framework for Dose Optimization Studies
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Xuemin", "Gu", email = "xuemin.gu@bicycletx.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Cong", "Xu", role = "aut"),
    person("Lei", "Xu", role = "aut"),
    person("Ying", "Yuan", role = "aut")
  )
Description: A frequentist framework for one-stage randomized dose optimization
    studies using clinically interpretable utility scores to integrate binary
    efficacy and safety endpoints. Implements sample size determination via
    normal approximation and exact multinomial methods, analytical expressions
    for selection-induced bias in response rate estimation, and plugin
    estimators for Type I error inflation in confirmatory trials. Includes
    the ROSE (Randomized Optimal Selection) design as a special case.
    Supports time-to-event confirmatory endpoint analysis with landmark
    survival, one-sample exponential, and two-sample Cox/log-rank tests.
